metadata.name: Followed tags GET /api/v1/followed_tags with limit param sets the correct pagination header for the prev path

sql_query.sql: SELECT 1 AS one FROM "oauth_access_tokens" WHERE "oauth_access_tokens"."token" = $1 LIMIT $2
SELECT 1 AS one FROM "oauth_access_tokens" WHERE "oauth_access_tokens"."token" = $1 AND "oauth_access_tokens"."id" != $2 LIMIT $3

SELECT "tag_follows"."id" AS t0_r0, "tag_follows"."tag_id" AS t0_r1, "tag_follows"."account_id" AS t0_r2, "tag_follows"."created_at" AS t0_r3, "tag_follows"."updated_at" AS t0_r4, "tags"."id" AS t1_r0, "tags"."name" AS t1_r1, "tags"."created_at" AS t1_r2, "tags"."updated_at" AS t1_r3, "tags"."usable" AS t1_r4, "tags"."trendable" AS t1_r5, "tags"."listable" AS t1_r6, "tags"."reviewed_at" AS t1_r7, "tags"."requested_review_at" AS t1_r8, "tags"."last_status_at" AS t1_r9, "tags"."max_score" AS t1_r10, "tags"."max_score_at" AS t1_r11, "tags"."display_name" AS t1_r12 FROM "tag_follows" INNER JOIN "tags" ON "tags"."id" = "tag_follows"."tag_id" WHERE "tag_follows"."account_id" = $1 ORDER BY "tag_follows"."id" DESC LIMIT $2
